<chapter id='xmlheaderdef'><title>Header</title>
  <para>
    header:: (<link linkend='xmlcelldef'>cell+</link>)
  </para>
  <para>
    <table frame="all"><title>Attributes</title>
      <tgroup cols='3' align='left' colsep='1' rowsep='1'>
        <thead><row>
            <entry>Name></entry><entry>Type</entry><entry>Default</entry>
        </row></thead>
        <tbody>
          <!--&commonattriblink;-->
          <row><entry><link linkend='common_attribs'>Common Attributes</link></entry></row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>
  </para>
  <formalpara><title>Description</title>
    <para>
      The <code>header</code> is a row printed at the begin of a
      <link linkend='groupdef'>group</link> or a <link linkend='xmlbodydef'>
        body</link>.  The <code>header</code> consists of one or a list of
      <link linkend='xmlcelldef'>cell</link>'s (See <link linkend='xmlbodydef'>
        body</link> for more information on how to setup.  The
      <code>header</code> is printed once at the begin of the block.
    </para>
  </formalpara>
</chapter>
